# ICD-11 Search Application - Project Intelligence

## Project Overview
This is a full-stack application for searching WHO ICD-11 medical codes, built with Next.js frontend and NestJS backend. It features Redis caching for performance optimization.

## Critical Implementation Patterns

### Frontend Patterns
- Next.js page structure with TypeScript
- Search interface with real-time feedback
- Responsive design for all device types
- Accessible UI components (WCAG 2.1 AA compliance)
- Client-side caching for performance

### Backend Patterns
- NestJS modular architecture
- Redis caching for WHO API responses
- Circuit breaker pattern for API resilience
- Typed DTOs for data transfer
- Strategy pattern for different caching approaches

### API Integration
- OAuth2 for WHO API authentication
- Rate limiting compliance
- Response normalization
- Error handling and retries

### Performance Patterns
- Redis caching with appropriate TTL
- Client-side state management
- Optimized search algorithm
- Bundle size optimization

## Project Structure
```
icd11-nextjs-nestjs-boilerplate/
├── frontend/            # Next.js frontend application
│   ├── pages/           # Routes and page components
│   ├── components/      # Reusable UI components
│   ├── hooks/           # Custom React hooks
│   ├── services/        # API client and services
│   ├── types/           # TypeScript definitions
│   └── styles/          # Global styles
│
├── backend/             # NestJS backend API
│   ├── src/
│   │   ├── main.ts      # Application entry point
│   │   ├── app.module.ts # Root module
│   │   ├── icd11/       # ICD11 module for WHO API
│   │   ├── cache/       # Redis cache module
│   │   └── common/      # Shared utilities and interfaces
│   └── test/            # Test files
│
├── docs/                # Project documentation and Memory Bank
└── docker/              # Docker configuration
```

## Memory Bank Documentation
The Memory Bank documentation is organized in the following structure:
- `projectbrief.md` - Core project requirements and goals
- `productContext.md` - Problem statement and UX goals
- `systemPatterns.md` - Architecture and design patterns
- `techContext.md` - Technology stack and requirements
- `activeContext.md` - Current focus and priorities
- `progress.md` - Implemented and pending work
- `decisions.md` - Technical decisions log

## Development Workflow
1. Configure local environment with .env files
2. Start backend NestJS application
3. Start frontend Next.js application
4. Implement features using TypeScript throughout
5. Document all significant decisions and patterns

## Known Challenges
1. WHO API integration complexity
2. Optimal caching strategy implementation
3. Search performance optimization
4. Design system selection and implementation

## Project Evolution
The project is currently in the initial setup phase, with only basic boilerplate structures in place. Key next steps include:
1. WHO API integration on the backend
2. Search UI implementation on the frontend
3. Redis caching configuration
4. Docker setup for development

## Tool Usage
- Next.js for frontend development
- NestJS for backend API
- Redis for caching
- TypeScript throughout the stack
- Docker for containerization (planned)

## Security Considerations
- WHO API credentials must be properly secured
- Redis instance should be configured securely
- Input validation required on all endpoints
- HTTPS enforced for all connections
- Content Security Policy implementation 